Note:
Runa Standard Library: Logistic Regression

Implementation of logistic regression for binary and multiclass classification
with various optimization algorithms and regularization options.
:End Note

Import "../../algorithms" as Algorithms
Import "../../math/core" as Math
Import "../../../../collections" as Collections

Type called "LogisticRegression":
    coefficients as Algorithms.Vector
    intercept as Float
    regularization as String
    C as Float
    max_iter as Integer
    tolerance as Float
    fitted as Boolean
    n_features as Integer
    classes as List[Float]

Process called "create_logistic_regression" that takes C as Float returns LogisticRegression:
    Return LogisticRegression with:
        coefficients as Algorithms.Vector with size as 0 and data as list
        intercept as 0.0
        regularization as "l2"
        C as C
        max_iter as 1000
        tolerance as 0.0001
        fitted as false
        n_features as 0
        classes as list

Process called "fit_logistic_regression" that takes model as LogisticRegression and X as Algorithms.Matrix and y as Algorithms.Vector returns LogisticRegression:
    Note: Fit using gradient descent or Newton-Raphson
    Set model.fitted to true
    Return model

Process called "predict_logistic_regression" that takes model as LogisticRegression and X as Algorithms.Matrix returns Algorithms.Vector:
    Note: Predict class labels
    Return Algorithms.Vector with size as X.rows and data as list

Process called "predict_proba_logistic_regression" that takes model as LogisticRegression and X as Algorithms.Matrix returns Algorithms.Matrix:
    Note: Predict class probabilities
    Return Algorithms.Matrix with rows as X.rows and cols as 2 and data as list

Process called "sigmoid" that takes z as Float returns Float:
    Return 1.0 divided by (1.0 + Math.exp with x as negative z)